1. Install the OS (Ubuntu 11.04) on /dev/sda of system volume server, and configure the network.
   (1) Use the entire disk of /dev/sda to install OS
   (2) Install the openssh server

2. Change your privilege to root.

3. Execute SystemVolumeDeploy.sh. The script will do the following things:
   (1) Install GlusterFS 3.2.3 and nfs-common
   (2) Create two directory /export1 and /export2
   (3) Mount /dev/sdb on /export2 
   (4) Create a GlusterFS volume using /export1 and /export2 as bricks (replica two)
   (5) Return a mount point (xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx:/SystemVolume)
   (6) Modify /etc/fstab to mount /dev/sdb automatically
   (7) Modify /etc/rc.local to start GlusterFS services automatically every rebooting

